data_table.description: Data contain extensive medical history information, describing general physical and psychological health of participating subjects (all > 65 years of age). Emphasis is given to auditory, visual, respiratory, cardio-vascular functions, medications/supplements taken, cognitive and emotional well being and subjects' mobility/independence and movement limitations. Lifestyle information is provided through variables querying for alcohol consumption, dietary, exercise and smoking habits. Data were collected at year 9.
